##Chun Yeung estate isolation diary 01 | 4 March-7 March

Micro signal

Features, life / Work / cat, and talk to you ~ 

At 7:30 pm on March 4, after a 10-hour journey back to Hong Kong from Wuhan, we arrived at Junyang estate in fo Tan and began a 14-day quarantine.

Chun Yeung estate in fo Tan is a public rental housing estate about to be occupied.

People returning from Hubei live in building 2.

My Room is at the end of one of the hallways on the 19th floor.

The way back to Hong Kong -- Florida

Ps: There is also a Vlog at the end of the Post

For those of you who have lived in Hong Kong, this room alone is not a small one. When reading a few people share a rent, per capita area is not necessarily larger than this unit.

High School began to live on campus dormitory life, six bed to table, there is a separate bathroom but no hot water, have to go to the bathhouse to take a bath, or some boys choose to take a shower.

When I got to college, my dorm in Beijing was a three-bed six-bed room with a table and a chair for each of us, plus a locker (mine was high, and I often had to build stools to get things) . Girl things more than ten square space to walk are afraid to break things. Although a bit crowded, but in the imperial capital, the East five ring a year 1500 yuan price also includes heating water and electricity with air conditioning and a separate toilet with hot water, what bicycle?

When I was a graduate student in Hong Kong, I shared a one-bedroom and one-room living room with three old classmates from Guangzhou University. The average rent was HK $10,000 per month. There were two bunk beds in the bedroom, and the sister who slept on top of me had the same undergraduate formula. Outside the living room two big desks a fight, transform into a public learning space and dining room.

There's nothing wrong with living close to each other. The key is to get along with roommates and work on different habits. (thanks for the tolerance of my former roommates, who are always pushing everyone to clean up) 

The living environment in Hong Kong will be better adapted to the transition from group accommodation. It's just that as you get older, your need for privacy grows. No matter the size, the small space that has been elaborately arranged is a warm home.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Folders and checklists at the door of the room

Arriving at Chun Yeung estate at around 7:30 pm, I checked into my room and had my first dinner of the Day: Light Porridge, red kidney beans, vegetables. After wearing the mask for almost 10 hours, he finally took it off.

The luggage was brought to the door of the room by the staff around 10 o'clock. There was a little rain on the suitcase. The second flight had just landed.

Lesson learned: Try to take your charging plug with you at all times. If you check it in your luggage, you may face a power outage

A few journalist friends contacted me on Wechat a few days in advance and asked if they could video-record the journey back to Hong Kong (the material is basically the one in front) .

At Heart, I am still a media person. Now I can participate in recording this experience and take some video data. It makes sense to be a temporary reporter in the epidemic area.

Friends, family and co-workers have been sending greetings, saying they recognize me in a news APP or on the television, or recognize the voice in a video. Jun Yang Estate also equipped with a small TV, sure enough in TVB to see the "Miss Ye" video. That's how you know a true love friend

According to the instructions, take off all the clothes you have worn today and seal them with a bag. Don't bring them home until you leave. Soak them in hot water. Wash your hair with a special hand sanitizer on the first day.

There was no toothpaste, WHATSAPP sent staff for supplies and ended up brushing his teeth with water before going to bed that night.

From the wechat clusters in Hubei and Wuhan, to the new ones in Junyang estate, to the car friends who went to the airport, they also built a "crunchen-wuhan" group.

Really is a friend of life and death, under an epidemic, usually noisy (non-derogatory, hot character causes) Wuhan People, now quite unity. Talk about the style and taste of the food, when it will be delivered, what materials are missing, how to apply for replacement, the room can not open the water heater how to do... no brainstorming can not solve the problem.

One Camper who didn't have a Hong Kong phone card was unable to call for supplies or scan a qr code to fill out online forms. Someone on Wechat immediately placed an order for her on WHATSAPP, and then a staff member sent her a phone card.

When I think of my grandparents, who are in their 70s, on the way to the airport, if they didn't know how to use Wechat, what would it be like to spend 14 days in a small, isolated room.

There are also elderly people who live alone and can't type, and children who live outside join our wechat group.

Disasters enhance human empathy, and we are not unrelated.

The stranded people from the epidemic area to pick up early or late, the use of the housing has not been paid for the isolation camp, labor and material costs... The government is facing great pressure.

Wechat group, we encourage each other, be sure to eat a good sleep.

We're GONNA make it, and we're GONNA get out of here in one piece.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Jun Yang Estate Trivia: How did the name of each building come from

The second flight, which originally took off at 6 pm, was delayed. The Campers who arrived later checked in around the clock and waited for their luggage to pack up until nearly 2 or 3 pm before going to bed. From noon to early morning, the way home is not easy.

Although there are difficult and thoughtless places, but the thought of so many staff outside to arrange hundreds of personal matters, we all more considerate, try to help each other to solve the difficulties, but also to minimize the requirements.

Place the completed menu in a folder by the door and lie down on a hard bed.

Bed Board only a thin cushion, really hard to the bone pain, can only try to roll up a section of the quilt cushion under the body.

Before going to bed, and long-term contact with the old classmate long video call, the last call may have been almost a year. She returned from Jiangsu to Shanghai to resume work, is home quarantine.

We talk about each other these two years some changes and perceptions, as if friends of the same age at this stage, these two years will have some sad mood, self-doubt, confusion about the future.

The same is true in Wuhan, Long Time and old friends do not call more than 2 hours.

But there were a lot of these late-night chats while we were in quarantine.

Physical Distance, can even close the emotional distance.

He didn't go to sleep until around 3:00 a.m.

During the outbreak, and especially after the night of Feb. 6, when news of Dr. Li's death was expected to improve, I fell asleep at this time almost every day, getting up at 9 a.m. to start an online work meeting.

My biological clock is set to sleep more than six hours a day, and my normal sleep time is between 1 and 8 o'clock.

The outbreak also pushed my mom's biological clock back to this time.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Some of these vintage towels say, "to Ankang. " 

March 5,2020

Around 8:40, the doorbell rings, and the first breakfast is served.

The staff set the meal down on a stool in the doorway.

According to the order, it's rice balls this morning. Rice balls are the soul of Sticky Rice bread Youtiao replacement, when I was a child in Hubu alley there is a shop I often buy too early, to strange taste, that is, both sugar and pickles, sweet and salty collocation is also called "salt and pepper. ".

As the breakfast spread dwindled, rice balls were an occasional substitute.

In 2020, the first meal of glutinous rice, too late to be served in Wuhan, was served in a detention camp in Hong Kong.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The doorbell rang again, bringing newspapers, masks and medical waste bags.

All Household / medical waste is packed in a single medical bag, tied tightly in a knot with plastic, and left at the door every morning before 10 am.

WHATSAPP called for toothpaste, and it finally came.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
After lunch, the doorbell rang again, and one of the staff members said they were going to get blood drawn and tested.

Walk up to an empty room on the 20th floor, another orientation of Chun Yeung estate, with views of the mountains not far away.

Two girls (Cantonese for "nurse") gave me a blood draw and a nasal swab.

Sitting on a stool, his head bobbing slightly, a cotton swab (probably) quickly and briefly jabbed into his nose.

After the tests, the girls immediately took off their rubber gloves and threw them away, washing their hands with alcohol-based handrub. Another member of staff led me back to the door.

Soon there is a staff room to collect the health questionnaire, asked the oral thermometer twice a day to take notes.

The symptoms of nasal congestion and runny nose have not been completely eliminated, nasal spray application has not yet been filled in, so truthfully filled in the symptoms.

After two hours, was napping at the door of the phone to wake up.

Due to nose-related symptoms, see a doctor on the ground floor below.

A special section has been set aside for consultation.

The doctor asks: How Long Does the symptom have? A: one or two years

Has It gotten worse in the last two weeks? A: No

For the nasal spray I was using, the doctor said it was best not to use it for more than five days in a row, and prescribed oral medication for nasal allergies.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In Wuhan Occasionally Rhinitis serious time, take medicine is not much effect.

Take turns to eat nasal allergy medicine, later also ate a week anti-inflammatory + Chinese Medicine Tongqiao rhinitis tablets, or almost. So every day before going to bed with a spray, otherwise can not fall asleep, during the day as much as possible to reduce the use of tolerance, but also afraid that there are some drug dependence.

More than 4:00 pm received a phone call to inquire about the condition of Rhinitis, the same problem and the doctor.

After I told the doctor that I had seen a doctor, I was told to take my temperature every day, and I would call every day to ask how I was doing.

It's in the 20s, and you still get the occasional stuffy nose.

Thanks to the omnipotent wechat group, there are the same rhinitis campers who remind of the dust factor.

The newly decorated room, the cement floor is indeed a lot of dust, TA in the room covered with a newspaper sprinkle water, the effect is not bad.

Today the weather turned fine, not like yesterday's rain, the evening also saw a little rosy clouds.

The second flight took off early, and new campers moved in just after 5:00 p.m.

The basketball court downstairs

One of the second group of students returned the night before, helping her driver contact a dozen others, working until late into the night in Florida, driver, age 60, was not familiar with the route in many places. Sister help teachers to call everyone, add wechat, add groups, and in accordance with you live in the region to re-pick up the route planning, so as to get to the airport earlier.

Annoyingly, some people give up chartered flights at the last minute for a variety of reasons, such as having an elderly mother to take care of at home. And early in the morning to register the Group of friends, there are also people who regret not to receive the first batch of notice to return to Hong Kong, can only wait for the next batch of arrangements.

Elder sister and many groups of friends together, 9,10 PM to eat dinner.

We apply for many times, but also try to endure, considering just arrived here hundreds of people to check in, testing, a variety of supplementary materials is really not a small workload.

March 6,2020

Morning after the morning meeting, began to code words on Wechat (the former) .

In the middle of writing, the computer crashed. Black screen doesn't work. The only good thing is that the previous draft has been temporarily saved as a work in progress in the web version.

Blood Lesson: important files should always be saved, and it's best to double back up in the cloud.

I was still thinking about what we needed to live with in the midst of an epidemic that has kept US indoors for at least 40 days, when our computers died and we couldn't send them out to be fixed.

The computer was forced to cross off the list of "essentials" .

Fortunately, there's an iPad that's barely passable, and you should always be ready for Plan B.

When the news came out, all of the more than 200 people we returned to Hong Kong on the first day tested negative.

We sincerely happy, not in vain at home to suppress more than 40 days!

The dinner received a letter of condolence from the Director of the Health Bureau, and a letter of condolence from the Hubei Association of Hong Kong.

Originally the Association had prepared a big gift bag including Lao Gan Ma tea, dim sum, toothpaste, toothbrush, etc. , but due to the many considerations of the camp (such as food safety, soliciting XX, etc.) and regulations, these packages can only be sent after we end our 14-day quarantine. Getting such a notice, everyone is more eager for the old godmother..

Fruit is really precious these days. If you eat the same boiled cabbage carrot mixed with baby corn for more than three days in a row, you can understand our desire for fruit.

The unified arrangement of the meal is not too bad, but Wuhan people at home after more than 40 days of strong taste to eat, all of a sudden change is not quite used to some.

A family sent Haidilao self-heating small hotpot, bask in the group has become the object of envy.

If it can circulate, the most valuable hard currency in the camps must be Lao Gan Ma!

Originally want to try to endure as much as possible, but also than in Wuhan isolation days to lower the standard of living.

But... after two barrels cup noodles finish eating, still can not help but discuss with Ni general arrangement that delivers material to me.

The first thing you want is a facial cleanser and, in addition to food, sports clothes.

Because the group is calling for keep aerobics! We can't be late

March 7,2020

Applied for a mop to do cleaning, to see if the symptoms of Rhinitis help, unexpectedly unexpectedly unexpectedly sent a full set of cleaning supplies, and even cleaning toilet spirit and toilet brush.

After a thorough cleaning, the layout of the room made a simple change, you can sit in the window in the direction of the sun, more like a "home. ".

Roommate said, clean up, ha ha ha, that's you.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
As if there had been some signs of a return to the south, the floor after mopping has been wet, not dry for a long time, hand-washed clothes are also, can only turn on the heater as a dryer.

The good news is, the rhinitis is much better.

A sensitive nose is the gold standard for checking air quality.

Afternoon Group of friends saw the ambulance downstairs, there is a person dragging the luggage on board, we are worried about whether there is a positive test results.

Soon after I saw on the news that one of the Campers on the second flight the next day had tested positive.

There was a little bit of concern, especially from people who were on the same flight.

After a while, the client spoke in the crowd: After returning to Wuhan on January 20, Ta has not left home, the only way out is on the way to the airport. The notice also did not confirm the test results, and the ambulance was found before the wrong gender. But the press has been all over it.

"I'm really sorry. There's nothing wrong with me at all. I hope everyone on my flight is safe and healthy. "

No one is accusing. The Group of friends are encouraging and comforting them, praying that this is a false alarm, and wishing us all well.

Thanks NI total sent material!

The standard of living GOT QUALITATIVE LEAP!

Relatives to send supplies to the civil security team downstairs to register, security, such as scissors and other sharp items and unpackaged food can not be sent in.

The most regrettable is the Haidilao self-heating small hotpot failed to pass the inspection, there is no specific reason is not to send

What's the first thing you want to do when this epidemic is over?

A lot of people must be the same, is want to eat hot pot.

Hot Pot is a lot of people get together to eat more flavor, round hot pot, is a reunion.

On December 31,2019, my New Year's Eve celebration was to have the most lavish Haidilao dinner in Shenzhen with some friends.

This winter, there is no reunion dinner, there is no new year, there is no new year ceremony... too long too long not with many people together.

Perhaps what we really want is a lively "reunion" .

We longed for an early reunion, as did our new friends in the camps.

It was quarantine, but the common battle brought everyone to the United front.

Listening to the local accent in the wechat group every day, using Wuhan Hanhanhanhua, and even watching everyone sing and dance, is the biggest source of happiness!

We are not cut off from each other by our isolation,

It's about reconnecting

It's like,

These two days because of the previous article and added the new friends of Wechat.

Thank you for your attention and recognition, willing to chat with me a few dollars of the day

Thank you for reading this at the end of the piece.

Look forward to the end of the epidemic, we can meet as soon as possible!
